DESCRIPTION:**Day 3 — Cultural Heritage**\n- 07:30 Breakfast: Cafe Centr
 al — try their veggie omelette\, ~₹150/person\n- 09:30 Morning: Se Cat
 hedral (open 09:30–18:00\, free entry) — a historic cathedral in Old G
 oa\, showcasing stunning Portuguese architecture\n  → Transport: Hire a 
 shared taxi from Colva to Se Cathedral\, ~₹1\,000 for 3 people\, 45 minu
 tes\n- 13:00 Lunch: Viva Panjim Restaurant — recommended: their veggie x
 acuti\, ~₹350/person\n- 15:00 Afternoon: Basilica of Bom Jesus (open 09:
 30–18:00\, free entry) — a UNESCO World Heritage Site and one of the o
 ldest churches in Goa\n  → Transport: Walk from Viva Panjim Restaurant t
 o Basilica of Bom Jesus\, 10 minutes\n- 19:00 Sunset: Miramar Beach — en
 joy the stunning views of the Arabian Sea\n- 20:00 Dinner: The Black Sheep
  Bistro — must-try: their veggie quinoa bowl\, ~₹400/person\n- Local t
 ip: Visit the local market near Se Cathedral to buy traditional Goan handi
